Pot. Deep bowl. Nine fragments of a large green glazed vessel. Base missing. Traces of carination on one sherd. Large raised moulding situated 11.0 cm below rim with thin yellow border and diagonal stripes of alternate black and white glaze. Rim: slightly flaring, swollen flattened top decorated with alternate black and white chevrons bordered by thin yellow lines. One sherd survives with part of a cuneiform inscription in yellow glaze, viz. ? (mat) Ash-shur. (Three decorated sherds drawn and rim sherd photographed.)
